  20. (** Composite change and mismatches *)
  21. type ('l,'r,'diff) mismatch =
  22.   | Name of {pos:int; got:string; expected:string; types_match:bool}
  23.   | Type of {pos:int; got:'l; expected:'r; reason:'diff}

  25. type ('l,'r,'diff) change =
  26.   | Change of ('l,'r,'diff) mismatch
  27.   | Swap of { pos: int * int; first: string; last: string }
  28.   | Move of {name:string; got:int; expected:int}
  29.   | Insert of {pos:int; insert:'r}
  30.   | Delete of {pos:int; delete:'l}

  32. let prefix ppf x =
  33.   let kind = match x with
  34.     | Change _ | Swap _ | Move _ -> Diffing.Modification
  35.     | Insert _ -> Diffing.Insertion
  36.     | Delete _ -> Diffing.Deletion
  37.   in
  38.   let style k ppf inner =
  39.     let sty = Diffing.style k in
  40.     Format.pp_open_stag ppf (Misc.Color.Style sty);
  41.     Format.kfprintf (fun ppf -> Format.pp_close_stag ppf () ) ppf inner
  42.   in
  43.   match x with
  44.   | Change (Name {pos; _ } | Type {pos; _})
  45.   | Insert { pos; _ } | Delete { pos; _ } ->
  46.       style kind ppf "%i. " pos
  47.   | Swap { pos = left, right; _ } ->
  48.       style kind ppf "%i<->%i. " left right
  49.   | Move { got; expected; _ } ->
  50.       style kind ppf "%i->%i. " expected got



  54. (** To detect [move] and [swaps], we are using the fact that
  55.     there are 2-cycles in the graph of name renaming.
  56.     - [Change (x,y,_) is then an edge from
  57.       [key_left x] to [key_right y].
  58.     - [Insert x] is an edge between the special node epsilon and
  59.       [key_left x]
  60.     - [Delete x] is an edge between [key_right] and the epsilon node
  61.       Since for 2-cycle, knowing one edge is enough to identify the cycle
  62.       it might belong to, we are using maps of partial 2-cycles.
  63. *)
  64. module Two_cycle: sig
  65.   type t = private (string * string)
  66.   val create: string -> string -> t
  67. end = struct
  68. ‌  type t = string * string
  69. ‌  let create kx ky =
  70.     if kx <= ky then kx, ky else ky, kx
  71. end
  72. module Swap = Map.Make(struct
  73.     type t = Two_cycle.t
  74.     let compare: t -> t -> int = Stdlib.compare
  75.   end)
  76. module Move = Misc.Stdlib.String.Map

  106.     (** Partial 2-cycles *)
  107.     type ('l,'r) partial_cycle =
  108.       | Left of int * D.state * 'l
  109.       | Right of int * D.state * 'r
  110.       | Both of D.state * 'l * 'r

  112.     (** Compute the partial cycle and edge associated to an edge *)
  113.     let edge state (x:left) (y:right) =
  114.       let kx, ky = key_left x.data, key_right y.data in
  115.       let edge =
  116.         if kx <= ky then
  117.           Left (x.pos, state, (x,y))
  118.         else
  119.           Right (x.pos,state, (x,y))
  120.       in
  121.       Two_cycle.create kx ky, edge

  123.     let merge_edge ex ey = match ex, ey with
  124.       | ex, None -> Some ex
  125.       | Left (lpos, lstate, l), Some Right (rpos, rstate,r)
  126.       | Right (rpos, rstate,r), Some Left (lpos, lstate, l) ->
  127.           let state = if lpos < rpos then rstate else lstate in
  128.           Some (Both (state,l,r))
  129.       | Both _ as b, _ | _, Some (Both _ as b)  -> Some b
  130.       | l, _ -> Some l

  132.     let two_cycles state changes =
  133.       let add (state,(swaps,moves)) (d:change) =
  134.         update d state,
  135.         match d with
  136.         | Change (x,y,_) ->
  137.             let k, edge = edge state x y in
  138.             Swap.update k (merge_edge edge) swaps, moves
  139.         | Insert nx ->
  140.             let k = key_right nx.data in
  141.             let edge = Right (nx.pos, state,nx) in
  142.             swaps, Move.update k (merge_edge edge) moves
  143.         | Delete nx ->
  144.             let k, edge = key_left nx.data, Left (nx.pos, state, nx) in
  145.             swaps, Move.update k (merge_edge edge) moves
  146.         | _ -> swaps, moves
  147.       in
  148.       List.fold_left add (state,(Swap.empty,Move.empty)) changes

  150.     (** Check if an edge belongs to a known 2-cycle *)
  151.     let swap swaps x y =
  152.       let kx, ky = key_left x.data, key_right y.data in
  153.       let key = Two_cycle.create kx ky in
  154.       match Swap.find_opt key swaps with
  155.       | None | Some (Left _ | Right _)-> None
  156.       | Some Both (state, (ll,lr),(rl,rr)) ->
  157.           match test state ll rr,  test state rl lr with
  158.           | Ok _, Ok _ ->
  159.               Some ({pos=ll.pos; data=kx}, {pos=rl.pos; data=ky})
  160.           | Error _, _ | _, Error _ -> None

  162.     let move moves x =
  163.       let name =
  164.         match x with
  165.         | Either.Left x -> key_left x.data
  166.         | Either.Right x -> key_right x.data
  167.       in
  168.       match Move.find_opt name moves with
  169.       | None | Some (Left _ | Right _)-> None
  170.       | Some Both (state,got,expected) ->
  171.           match test state got expected with
  172.           | Ok _ ->
  173.               Some (Move {name; got=got.pos; expected=expected.pos})
  174.           | Error _ -> None

  176.     let refine state patch =
  177.       let _, (swaps, moves) = two_cycles state patch in
  178.       let filter: change -> composite_change option = function
  179.         | Keep _ -> None
  180.         | Insert x ->
  181.             begin match move moves (Either.Right x) with
  182.             | Some _ as move -> move
  183.             | None -> Some (Insert {pos=x.pos;insert=x.data})
  184.             end
  185.         | Delete x ->
  186.             begin match move moves (Either.Left x) with
  187.             | Some _ -> None
  188.             | None -> Some (Delete {pos=x.pos; delete=x.data})
  189.             end
  190.         | Change(x,y, reason) ->
  191.             match swap swaps x y with
  192.             | Some ({pos=pos1; data=first}, {pos=pos2; data=last}) ->
  193.                 if x.pos = pos1 then
  194.                   Some (Swap { pos = pos1, pos2; first; last})
  195.                 else None
  196.             | None -> Some (Change reason)
  197.       in
  198.       List.filter_map filter patch
